
📘 Study.OS

A modern study management system designed to optimize learning, increase productivity, and help students perform at a higher level.

📌 Overview

Study.OS is a structured study system built to help students organize their academic routine with clarity and efficiency.

The project focuses on:

Strategic planning

Task organization

Performance tracking

Study optimization techniques

Study.OS is designed to transform unstructured study habits into a consistent, measurable, and high-performance workflow.

🎯 Purpose

The main goal of Study.OS is to provide a system that:

Improves focus and productivity

Reduces procrastination

Organizes subjects and priorities

Tracks academic progress

Encourages discipline and consistency

⚙️ Core Features

📂 Structured subject organization

🗓️ Weekly and daily study planning

⏱️ Time management system

📊 Progress tracking

🧠 Evidence-based study strategies

🔁 Continuous improvement model

🧱 System Philosophy

Study.OS is based on the idea that:

Studying is not about spending more time — it’s about using better systems.

The project applies operating system logic to academic life:

Inputs (content)

Processing (active study methods)

Output (performance results)

Feedback loop (progress analysis).